bottom of your garage door.";i:12;s:67:"This infrared sensor passes a beam horizontally across the opening.";i:13;s:183:"Incorrect travel settings When your garage door is installed the opener is programmed with a number that indicates how far down the door is expected to travel before its fully closed.";i:14;s:167:"If the door closes before that set distance has been completed then the opener thinks theres an error and automatically reverses to prevent property damages or injury.";i:15;s:85:"If your garage door opens and suddenly stops it might be because of your logic board.";i:16;s:60:"The logic board receives and responds signals to any remote.";i:17;s:110:"You might need to consider replacing it if your door is not working properly or you may purchase a new opener.";i:18;s:127:"If the door closes while holding the button pressed you are likely having one of the following issues with your safety sensors.";i:19;s:53:"The solution is usually one or more of the following.";i:20;s:60:"The sensors are dirty - Wipe lenses with a clean soft cloth.";i:21;s:103:"They are misaligned This is the most likely problem and the most common issue with Garage Door openers.";i:22;s:71:"Overhead garage door opens and closes randomly on its own in the night.";i:23;s:270:"Post by Shannon Fri Sep 27 2019 619 pm Ya that weather station has been there for years so not sure its the culprit and as far as we know this is an isolated event although dad says he has closed that door a couple times in past years thinking he had done it previously.";i:24;s:140:"Turn the down limit switch screw clockwise one turn with a flat blade screwdriver if the garage door closes and then begins to open back up.";i:25;s:112:"The garage door will automatically go in reverse whenever it hits an obstruction such as the driveway or ground.";i:26;s:40:"Try to operate the garage door manually.";i:27;s:76:"This helps you determine if the problem is related to the door or the motor.";i:28;s:119:"The garage door can be operated manually by disconnecting the garage door opener from the door using the red pull cord.";i:29;s:66:"If the door is working properly it should be easy to lift by hand.";i:30;s:162:"My Garage Door Opens Partially Then Stops Overhead Of The Inland Empire What To Do When Your Garage Door Opens And Closes By Itself Why Won T My Garage Door Open.";i:31;s:37:"Fold a soft cloth around your finger.";i:32;s:62:"Locate the lens on each side of the garage door at the bottom.";i:33;s:92:"The lenses will most likely be attached to metal brackets attached to the garage-door frame.";i:34;s:109:"Another possibility if the door opens andor closes at random is the wiring at the control button on the wall.";i:35;s:86:"If the control button is hardwired to the unit any short could cause strange behavior.";i:36;s:87:"Its a good idea to disconnect power to the opener before checking the wire connections.";i:37;s:191:"When a garage door descends on command but then immediately reverses itself the problem is usually with the sensor eyes along the side tracks or with the doors wheels binding in their tracks.";i:38;s:146:"But when the door begins to descend all on its own the problem may point to the openers logic board or the circuitry inside the motor unit itself.";i:39;s:39:"The garage door goes down then back up.";i:40;s:49:"Your garage door opens immediately after closing.";i:41;s:40:"The garage door keeps going up and down.";i:42;s:47:"Your garage door opens when it hits the ground.";i:43;s:39:"Garage door opener keeps going back up.";i:44;s:34:"It may be your garage door sensor.";i:45;s:101:"There are four common problems with garage door sensors three of these homeowners can fix themselves.";i:46;s:106:"First of all you need to diagnose the issue and discover whats stopping the door from opening all the way.";i:47;s:113:"To determine if the root cause is the automatic opener or the garage door itself follow these three simple steps.";i:48;s:26:"Close the door completely.";i:49;s:78:"Pull the emergency release cord to disengage the opener trolley from the door.";i:50;s:140:"Turn the down limit switch screw clockwise one turn with a flat blade screwdriver if the garage door closes and then begins to open back up.";i:51;s:49:"The garage door will automatically go in reverse.";i:52;s:134:"The garage door will close completely and then continue moving in the reverse direction leaving you with a partially open garage door.";i:53;s:210:"The same thing can happen with the open limit once the door is all the way open on the tracks if that limit is set too high it doesnt register and will continue in motion until you have a partially closed door.";}}